intro: 
  - excerpt: 'I am physicist with (real) interest in biology. I did my PhD in the Center for Molecular Biology Severo Ochoa in Madrid (CSIC-UAM) under the supervision of Dr. Ugo Bastolla. I moved then to
  the Microbial Ecology laboratory of Imperial College London leaded by Dr. Thomas Bell where I am Research Associate. I focus on complex biological systems at different scales, from molecules to large ecosystems, and I like to consider experimental data whenever is possible. In the following, I briefly describe some areas of interest, from microscopic to macroscopic systems.'
